not be reduced uncritically to interpretations based in much later Inca histories of the Andean highlands. Instead, the author seeks the origins of Moche mural art, and its emphasis on figuration, in the deep past of the Pacific coast of South America. Image Encounters shows how formal transformations in Moche mural art, before and after the seventh century, were part of broader changes to the work that images were made to perform at Huacas de Moche, El Brujo, Pañamarca, and elsewhere in an increasingly complex social and political world. In doing so, this book reveals alternative evidentiary foundations for histories of art and visual experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHuacaszPeru. 0aIndian mural painting and decoration. 0aIndians of South AmericaxAntiquities. 0aMochica IndianszPeruzPañamarca SitexAntiquities. 0aMochica IndianszPeruzPañamarca SitexAntiquities. 0aMochica mural painting and decorationzPeruzPañamarca Site. 0aMochica mural painting and decorationzPeruzPañamarca Site. 0aMural painting and decoration, Peruvian. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aMoche art, Moche, mural art, Peruvian art, art history, archaeology, Pre-Columbian, pre-columbian art, pre-columbian archaeology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2022z9783110992793oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076651640uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32426440uhttps://www.